      "## update\n\n`client.apps.update(id: string, app_store_description?: string, app_type?: 'b2b_app' | 'b2c_app' | 'company_app' | 'component', base_url?: string, dashboard_path?: string, description?: string, discover_path?: string, experience_path?: string, icon?: { id?: string; direct_upload_id?: string; }, name?: string, oauth_client_type?: 'public' | 'confidential', openapi_path?: string, production_android_build_id?: string, production_ios_build_id?: string, production_web_build_id?: string, redirect_uris?: string[], required_scopes?: string[], route?: string, secrets?: object, skills_path?: string, status?: 'live' | 'unlisted' | 'hidden'): { id: string; account: object; api_key: object; app_store_description: string; app_type: 'b2b_app' | 'b2c_app' | 'company_app' | 'component'; base_url: string; creator: object; dashboard_path: string; default_api_key: object; description: string; discover_path: string; domain_id: string; experience_path: string; hosted_url: string; icon: object; marketplace_status: 'not_available' | 'pending_review' | 'live_marketplace'; name: string; oauth_client_type: 'public' | 'confidential'; openapi_path: string; origin: string; product_id: string; production_android_build: object; production_ios_build: object; production_web_build: object; redirect_uris: string[]; requested_permissions: object[]; route: string; secrets: object; skills_path: string; status: 'live' | 'unlisted' | 'hidden'; verified: boolean; }`\n\n**patch** `/apps/{id}`\n\nUpdates the settings, metadata, or status of an app. Fields that are omitted keep their current value.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `id: string`\n\n- `app_store_description?: string`\n  The detailed description shown on the app store's in-depth app view page.\n\n- `app_type?: 'b2b_app' | 'b2c_app' | 'company_app' | 'component'`\n  The type of end-user the app is built for.\n\n- `base_url?: string`\n  The base production URL where the app is hosted.\n\n- `dashboard_path?: string`\n  The URL path for the company dashboard view.\n\n- `description?: string`\n  A short description of the app shown in listings and search results.\n\n- `discover_path?: string`\n  The URL path for the discover view.\n\n- `experience_path?: string`\n  The URL path for the member-facing hub view, such as `/experiences/[experienceId]`.\n\n- `icon?: { id?: string; direct_upload_id?: string; }`\n  The icon image for the app in PNG, JPEG, or GIF format, referencing an uploaded file: `{ id }` for an existing attachment or `{ direct_upload_id }` for a new direct upload.\n  - `id?: string`\n    The tag of an already-uploaded attachment.\n  - `direct_upload_id?: string`\n    The signed id of a completed direct upload.\n\n- `name?: string`\n  The display name for the app, shown to users on the app store and product pages.\n\n- `oauth_client_type?: 'public' | 'confidential'`\n  How the app authenticates at the OAuth token endpoint.\n\n- `openapi_path?: string`\n  The URL path to the app's OpenAPI spec file (requires the ai_chat capability).\n\n- `production_android_build_id?: string`\n  The app build (`abld_` tag) to serve as the Android production build, or `null` to unassign it. Same rules as `production_web_build_id`.\n\n- `production_ios_build_id?: string`\n  The app build (`abld_` tag) to serve as the iOS production build, or `null` to unassign it. Same rules as `production_web_build_id`.\n\n- `production_web_build_id?: string`\n  The app build (`abld_` tag) to serve as the web production build, or `null` to unassign it. The build must belong to this app, target web, and be in the draft or approved status; a draft build is queued for approval and takes over once approved. Requires the `developer:manage_builds` scope.\n\n- `redirect_uris?: string[]`\n  The whitelisted OAuth callback URLs users are redirected to after authorizing the app.\n\n- `required_scopes?: string[]`\n  The OAuth scopes the app requests from users when they install it.\n\n- `route?: string`\n  The subdomain route where the app's hosted web builds are served.\n\n- `secrets?: object`\n  Secrets to add or overwrite on the app, as an object of string values. Keys not included are left untouched; pass null or an empty string as the value to delete a secret. Encrypted at rest and injected into the app's hosted server runtime.\n\n- `skills_path?: string`\n  The URL path to the app's skills directory (requires the ai_chat capability).\n\n- `status?: 'live' | 'unlisted' | 'hidden'`\n  Controls the app's visibility. `live` publishes on Whop discovery (requires name, icon, and description); `unlisted` hides it from discovery while keeping direct-link access.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id: string; account: { id: string; title: string; }; api_key: { token: string; created_at: string; }; app_store_description: string; app_type: 'b2b_app' | 'b2c_app' | 'company_app' | 'component'; base_url: string; creator: { id: string; name: string; username: string; }; dashboard_path: string; default_api_key: { id: string; name: string; obfuscated_secret_key: string; secret_key: string; }; description: string; discover_path: string; domain_id: string; experience_path: string; hosted_url: string; icon: { url: string; }; marketplace_status: 'not_available' | 'pending_review' | 'live_marketplace'; name: string; oauth_client_type: 'public' | 'confidential'; openapi_path: string; origin: string; product_id: string; production_android_build: { id: string; checksum: string; file_url: string; source_url: string; status: 'draft' | 'pending' | 'approved' | 'rejected'; }; production_ios_build: { id: string; checksum: string; file_url: string; source_url: string; status: 'draft' | 'pending' | 'approved' | 'rejected'; }; production_web_build: { id: string; checksum: string; file_url: string; source_url: string; status: 'draft' | 'pending' | 'approved' | 'rejected'; }; redirect_uris: string[]; requested_permissions: { is_required: boolean; justification: string; permission_action: { action: string; name: string; }; }[]; route: string; secrets: object; skills_path: string; status: 'live' | 'unlisted' | 'hidden'; verified: boolean; }`\n\n  - `id: string`\n  - `account: { id: string; title: string; }`\n  - `api_key: { token: string; created_at: string; }`\n  - `app_store_description: string`\n  - `app_type: 'b2b_app' | 'b2c_app' | 'company_app' | 'component'`\n  - `base_url: string`\n  - `creator: { id: string; name: string; username: string; }`\n  - `dashboard_path: string`\n  - `default_api_key: { id: string; name: string; obfuscated_secret_key: string; secret_key: string; }`\n  - `description: string`\n  - `discover_path: string`\n  - `domain_id: string`\n  - `experience_path: string`\n  - `hosted_url: string`\n  - `icon: { url: string; }`\n  - `marketplace_status: 'not_available' | 'pending_review' | 'live_marketplace'`\n  - `name: string`\n  - `oauth_client_type: 'public' | 'confidential'`\n  - `openapi_path: string`\n  - `origin: string`\n  - `product_id: string`\n  - `production_android_build: { id: string; checksum: string; file_url: string; source_url: string; status: 'draft' | 'pending' | 'approved' | 'rejected'; }`\n  - `production_ios_build: { id: string; checksum: string; file_url: string; source_url: string; status: 'draft' | 'pending' | 'approved' | 'rejected'; }`\n  - `production_web_build: { id: string; checksum: string; file_url: string; source_url: string; status: 'draft' | 'pending' | 'approved' | 'rejected'; }`\n  - `redirect_uris: string[]`\n  - `requested_permissions: { is_required: boolean; justification: string; permission_action: { action: string; name: string; }; }[]`\n  - `route: string`\n  - `secrets: object`\n  - `skills_path: string`\n  - `status: 'live' | 'unlisted' | 'hidden'`\n  - `verified: boolean`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Whop from '@whop/sdk';\n\nconst client = new Whop();\n\nconst app = await client.apps.update('id');\n\nconsole.log(app);\n```",
