    markdown:
      "## list\n\n`client.people.list(account_id?: string, after?: string, before?: string, direction?: 'asc' | 'desc', filters?: string, first?: number, from?: string, sort?: string, to?: string): { id: string; account_id: string; first_seen_at: string; last_seen_at: string; person_id: string; purchase_count: number; ad_sets?: object[]; ads?: object[]; aov?: number; campaigns?: object[]; email?: string; has_failed_payment?: boolean; ltv?: number; name?: string; phone?: string; }`\n\n**get** `/people`\n\nLists the people (visitors and customers) of an account, aggregated from pixel events. The account is inferred from an account API key; other credentials must pass account_id.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `account_id?: string`\n  The ID of the account, which will look like biz_*************. Optional for account API keys; required for credentials that can access multiple accounts.\n\n- `after?: string`\n  A cursor for fetching people after a previous page.\n\n- `before?: string`\n  A cursor for fetching people before a later page.\n\n- `direction?: 'asc' | 'desc'`\n  Sort direction. Defaults to desc.\n\n- `filters?: string`\n  A JSON-encoded array of filters, each with field, operator, and value keys.\n\n- `first?: number`\n  The number of people to return (default 100, max 100).\n\n- `from?: string`\n  Start of the time range as an ISO 8601 timestamp. Defaults to 366 days before `to`.\n\n- `sort?: string`\n  Column to sort by (e.g. last_seen_at, ltv, purchase_count). Defaults to last_seen_at.\n\n- `to?: string`\n  End of the time range as an ISO 8601 timestamp. Defaults to now.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id: string; account_id: string; first_seen_at: string; last_seen_at: string; person_id: string; purchase_count: number; ad_sets?: { id: string; name?: string; thumbnail_url?: string; }[]; ads?: { id: string; name?: string; thumbnail_url?: string; }[]; aov?: number; campaigns?: { id: string; name?: string; thumbnail_url?: string; }[]; email?: string; has_failed_payment?: boolean; ltv?: number; name?: string; phone?: string; }`\n\n  - `id: string`\n  - `account_id: string`\n  - `first_seen_at: string`\n  - `last_seen_at: string`\n  - `person_id: string`\n  - `purchase_count: number`\n  - `ad_sets?: { id: string; name?: string; thumbnail_url?: string; }[]`\n  - `ads?: { id: string; name?: string; thumbnail_url?: string; }[]`\n  - `aov?: number`\n  - `campaigns?: { id: string; name?: string; thumbnail_url?: string; }[]`\n  - `email?: string`\n  - `has_failed_payment?: boolean`\n  - `ltv?: number`\n  - `name?: string`\n  - `phone?: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Whop from '@whop/sdk';\n\nconst client = new Whop();\n\n// Automatically fetches more pages as needed.\nfor await (const personListResponse of client.people.list()) {\n  console.log(personListResponse);\n}\n```",
