    markdown:
      "## create\n\n`client.transfers.create(amount: number, origin_id: string, currency?: string, destination_id?: string, expires_at?: string, idempotence_key?: string, metadata?: object, notes?: string, redeemable_count?: number, type?: 'ledger' | 'wallet_send' | 'claim_link', Idempotency-Key?: string): { id: string; amount: number; created_at: string; currency: string; destination: object | object; destination_ledger_account_id: string; origin: object | object; origin_ledger_account_id: string; fee_amount?: number; metadata?: object; notes?: string; } | { amount: string; currency: string; destination: object; object: 'send'; source: object; tx_hash: string; } | { id: string; amount: string; claim_url: string; currency: string; expires_at: string; object: 'claim_link'; redeemable_count: number; source: object; status: string; }`\n\n**post** `/transfers`\n\nMoves funds out of an account. `type` selects the kind of movement (default `ledger`): `ledger` transfers credit between two ledger accounts and returns a Transfer; `wallet_send` sends USDT from the origin account's Ethereum wallet to a recipient; `claim_link` funds a shareable claim link anyone with the URL can redeem.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `amount: number`\n  The amount to move, in the transfer currency. For example 25.00.\n\n- `origin_id: string`\n  The account sending the funds. A user ID (user_xxx), account ID (biz_xxx), or ledger account ID (ldgr_xxx).\n\n- `currency?: string`\n  Currency, such as `usd`. Required for ledger transfers.\n\n- `destination_id?: string`\n  The recipient. Required for ledger and wallet_send (a user_/biz_/ldgr_ ID, or — for sends — an email). Omit for claim_link.\n\n- `expires_at?: string`\n  claim_link only. Link expiry as an ISO 8601 timestamp. Defaults to 24 hours from creation.\n\n- `idempotence_key?: string`\n  Ledger transfers only. A unique key to prevent duplicate transfers.\n\n- `metadata?: object`\n  Ledger transfers only. Custom key-value pairs attached to the transfer. Max 50 keys, 100 chars per key, 500 chars per string value.\n\n- `notes?: string`\n  Ledger transfers only. A short note describing the transfer.\n\n- `redeemable_count?: number`\n  claim_link only. How many different users can claim the link. Defaults to 1.\n\n- `type?: 'ledger' | 'wallet_send' | 'claim_link'`\n  The kind of money movement. Defaults to ledger.\n\n- `Idempotency-Key?: string`\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id: string; amount: number; created_at: string; currency: string; destination: { id: string; typename: 'Company'; route?: string; title?: string; } | { id: string; typename: 'User'; name?: string; username?: string; }; destination_ledger_account_id: string; origin: { id: string; typename: 'Company'; route?: string; title?: string; } | { id: string; typename: 'User'; name?: string; username?: string; }; origin_ledger_account_id: string; fee_amount?: number; metadata?: object; notes?: string; } | { amount: string; currency: string; destination: { account_id: string; address: string; }; object: 'send'; source: { account_id: string; address: string; }; tx_hash: string; } | { id: string; amount: string; claim_url: string; currency: string; expires_at: string; object: 'claim_link'; redeemable_count: number; source: { account_id: string; }; status: string; }`\n  A transfer of credit between two ledger accounts.\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Whop from '@whop/sdk';\n\nconst client = new Whop();\n\nconst transfer = await client.transfers.create({ amount: 0, origin_id: 'origin_id' });\n\nconsole.log(transfer);\n```",
