    markdown:
      "## list\n\n`client.payouts.methods.list(account_id?: string, after?: string, amount?: number, before?: string, currency?: string, destination_currency?: string, destination_id?: string, first?: number, include_available?: boolean, last?: number, status?: 'created' | 'active' | 'broken', user_id?: string): { id: string; account_reference: string; created_at: string; destination_currency: string; institution_name: string; is_default: boolean; nickname: string; object: 'payout_method'; payer_name: string; payout_destination: object; quote: object; status: 'created' | 'active' | 'broken'; }`\n\n**get** `/payouts/methods`\n\nLists the saved payout methods (bank accounts, digital wallets, crypto addresses) that an account or user can withdraw to, most recently added first. Pass exactly one of account_id (a biz_ identifier) or user_id (a user_ identifier). Pass an amount to additionally get a fee and delivery quote per method for withdrawing that amount.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `account_id?: string`\n  The owning account ID (a biz_ identifier). Provide this or user_id.\n\n- `after?: string`\n  Cursor to fetch the page after (from page_info.end_cursor).\n\n- `amount?: number`\n  Optional withdrawal amount in whole currency units, for example `250.00`. When provided, each method includes a quote with the estimated fee, amount received, and delivery date for that amount.\n\n- `before?: string`\n  Cursor to fetch the page before (from page_info.start_cursor).\n\n- `currency?: string`\n  Currency code of the amount, for example `usd`. Only meaningful with amount.\n\n- `destination_currency?: string`\n  Currency the destination would deliver payouts in. Only meaningful with destination_id; required fields vary by destination currency.\n\n- `destination_id?: string`\n  Narrows available_destinations to this one destination (a pd_ identifier from a previous listing) and includes its required_fields — the values to collect to add it as a payout method. Implies include_available.\n\n- `first?: number`\n  Number of payout methods to return from the start of the window. Capped at 25 when an amount is provided.\n\n- `include_available?: boolean`\n  When true, the response also carries available_destinations — payout rails the account could add as a new payout method, with per-currency quotes when an amount is provided.\n\n- `last?: number`\n  Number of payout methods to return from the end of the window.\n\n- `status?: 'created' | 'active' | 'broken'`\n  Optional status filter. `created` means saved but unused, `active` means a payout through it succeeded, `broken` means the last payout failed and the method needs fixing.\n\n- `user_id?: string`\n  The owning user ID (a user_ identifier). Provide this or account_id.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id: string; account_reference: string; created_at: string; destination_currency: string; institution_name: string; is_default: boolean; nickname: string; object: 'payout_method'; payer_name: string; payout_destination: { delivery_type: string; icon_url: string; name: string; supports_instant_delivery: boolean; supports_standard_delivery: boolean; }; quote: { amount: number; currency: string; exchange_rate: number; instant: { estimated_arrival: string; fee: number; total_received: number; }; max_limit: number; min_limit: number; standard: { estimated_arrival: string; fee: number; total_received: number; }; }; status: 'created' | 'active' | 'broken'; }`\n\n  - `id: string`\n  - `account_reference: string`\n  - `created_at: string`\n  - `destination_currency: string`\n  - `institution_name: string`\n  - `is_default: boolean`\n  - `nickname: string`\n  - `object: 'payout_method'`\n  - `payer_name: string`\n  - `payout_destination: { delivery_type: string; icon_url: string; name: string; supports_instant_delivery: boolean; supports_standard_delivery: boolean; }`\n  - `quote: { amount: number; currency: string; exchange_rate: number; instant: { estimated_arrival: string; fee: number; total_received: number; }; max_limit: number; min_limit: number; standard: { estimated_arrival: string; fee: number; total_received: number; }; }`\n  - `status: 'created' | 'active' | 'broken'`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Whop from '@whop/sdk';\n\nconst client = new Whop();\n\n// Automatically fetches more pages as needed.\nfor await (const methodListResponse of client.payouts.methods.list()) {\n  console.log(methodListResponse);\n}\n```",
