    markdown:
      "## list\n\n`client.bounties.list(account_id?: string, after?: string, before?: string, created_after?: string, created_before?: string, direction?: 'asc' | 'desc', first?: number, last?: number, order?: 'created_at' | 'gross_paid_out_amount', query?: string, status?: 'scheduled' | 'open' | 'closed' | 'completed' | 'canceled', user_id?: string): { id: string; accepted_deliverable_types: 'content_url' | 'media' | 'data_capture'[]; accepted_submissions_count: number; accepted_submissions_limit: number; allowed_country_codes: string[]; budget_amount: number; business_goal_type: string; created_at: string; currency: string; experience_id: string; funding_account: object; gross_paid_out_amount: number; gross_reward_amount: number; poster: object; scheduled_frequency: 'once' | 'hourly' | 'daily' | 'weekly' | 'monthly'; scheduled_publish_at: string; spots_remaining: number; status: 'scheduled' | 'open' | 'closed' | 'completed' | 'canceled'; submissions_closed_at: string; title: string; unresolved_submissions_count: number; updated_at: string; }`\n\n**get** `/bounties`\n\nLists bounties visible to the credential — for an account API key, the account's bounties including scheduled drafts; for a user token, the bounties the user can see and work.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `account_id?: string`\n  Scope the list to this account (`biz_` tag). Requires read access to the account; account API keys may pass their own account or a connected account.\n\n- `after?: string`\n  Cursor to paginate forwards from.\n\n- `before?: string`\n  Cursor to paginate backwards from.\n\n- `created_after?: string`\n  Only bounties created after this ISO 8601 timestamp.\n\n- `created_before?: string`\n  Only bounties created before this ISO 8601 timestamp.\n\n- `direction?: 'asc' | 'desc'`\n  Sort direction.\n\n- `first?: number`\n  Number of bounties to return from the start of the window.\n\n- `last?: number`\n  Number of bounties to return from the end of the window.\n\n- `order?: 'created_at' | 'gross_paid_out_amount'`\n  Sort field.\n\n- `query?: string`\n  Substring match on the bounty title or ID.\n\n- `status?: 'scheduled' | 'open' | 'closed' | 'completed' | 'canceled'`\n  Filter by lifecycle state.\n\n- `user_id?: string`\n  List the bounties this user participated in (`user_` tag). Must be the authenticated user.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id: string; accepted_deliverable_types: 'content_url' | 'media' | 'data_capture'[]; accepted_submissions_count: number; accepted_submissions_limit: number; allowed_country_codes: string[]; budget_amount: number; business_goal_type: string; created_at: string; currency: string; experience_id: string; funding_account: { id: string; title: string; }; gross_paid_out_amount: number; gross_reward_amount: number; poster: { id: string; name: string; profile_picture: { url: string; }; username: string; }; scheduled_frequency: 'once' | 'hourly' | 'daily' | 'weekly' | 'monthly'; scheduled_publish_at: string; spots_remaining: number; status: 'scheduled' | 'open' | 'closed' | 'completed' | 'canceled'; submissions_closed_at: string; title: string; unresolved_submissions_count: number; updated_at: string; }`\n\n  - `id: string`\n  - `accepted_deliverable_types: 'content_url' | 'media' | 'data_capture'[]`\n  - `accepted_submissions_count: number`\n  - `accepted_submissions_limit: number`\n  - `allowed_country_codes: string[]`\n  - `budget_amount: number`\n  - `business_goal_type: string`\n  - `created_at: string`\n  - `currency: string`\n  - `experience_id: string`\n  - `funding_account: { id: string; title: string; }`\n  - `gross_paid_out_amount: number`\n  - `gross_reward_amount: number`\n  - `poster: { id: string; name: string; profile_picture: { url: string; }; username: string; }`\n  - `scheduled_frequency: 'once' | 'hourly' | 'daily' | 'weekly' | 'monthly'`\n  - `scheduled_publish_at: string`\n  - `spots_remaining: number`\n  - `status: 'scheduled' | 'open' | 'closed' | 'completed' | 'canceled'`\n  - `submissions_closed_at: string`\n  - `title: string`\n  - `unresolved_submissions_count: number`\n  - `updated_at: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Whop from '@whop/sdk';\n\nconst client = new Whop();\n\n// Automatically fetches more pages as needed.\nfor await (const bountyListItem of client.bounties.list()) {\n  console.log(bountyListItem);\n}\n```",
