    markdown:
      "## create\n\n`client.bountySubmissions.create(bounty_id: string, affiliate_code?: string, deliverable?: { type: 'content_url' | 'media' | 'data_capture'; caption?: string; file_ids?: string[]; urls?: string[]; }, metadata?: { city?: string; country?: string; device?: string; fov?: number; operator?: string; site?: string; station?: string; }, Idempotency-Key?: string): { id: string; bounty_id: string; capture_clips: bounty_capture_clip[]; capture_filename: string; captured_clip_count: number; captured_duration_seconds: number; city: string; content: string; country: string; created_at: string; deliverable_type: 'content_url' | 'media' | 'data_capture'; deliverable_urls: string[]; denial_reason: string; device: string; fov: number; operator: string; resolved_at: string; site: string; station: string; status: 'in_progress' | 'submitted' | 'approved' | 'denied'; submitted_at: string; updated_at: string; worker: object; }`\n\n**post** `/bounty_submissions`\n\nCreates a submission on a workforce bounty. For `content_url` and `media` bounties, include the matching `deliverable` payload and the submission goes straight to review — create is the only step. For `data_capture` bounties, omit the deliverable: this starts a claimed attempt whose proof accumulates server-side, and the separate submit endpoint sends it to review once complete. Requires a user credential — account API keys cannot author submissions.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `bounty_id: string`\n  The bounty to submit to (`bnty_` tag).\n\n- `affiliate_code?: string`\n  Affiliate code crediting the referrer, when the worker arrived through one.\n\n- `deliverable?: { type: 'content_url' | 'media' | 'data_capture'; caption?: string; file_ids?: string[]; urls?: string[]; }`\n  The submitted work, matching one of the bounty's accepted deliverable types.\n  - `type: 'content_url' | 'media' | 'data_capture'`\n    Deliverable shape. Must be accepted by the bounty's goal type.\n  - `caption?: string`\n    Optional written context shown to reviewers.\n  - `file_ids?: string[]`\n    Uploaded file IDs. Required when `type` is `media`.\n  - `urls?: string[]`\n    The posted content links, up to 10. Required when `type` is `content_url`.\n\n- `metadata?: { city?: string; country?: string; device?: string; fov?: number; operator?: string; site?: string; station?: string; }`\n  Optional capture metadata describing where and how the footage was recorded. Persisted on the submission. On a `data_capture` bounty every field except `fov` is required whenever metadata is provided.\n  - `city?: string`\n    City the footage was recorded in.\n  - `country?: string`\n    Country the footage was recorded in.\n  - `device?: string`\n    Device the footage was recorded on.\n  - `fov?: number`\n    Horizontal field of view in degrees.\n  - `operator?: string`\n    Identifier of the person who recorded the footage.\n  - `site?: string`\n    Site or venue the footage was recorded at.\n  - `station?: string`\n    Station or position within the site.\n\n- `Idempotency-Key?: string`\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id: string; bounty_id: string; capture_clips: { id: string; bounty_submission_id: string; created_at: string; duration_seconds: number; failure_code: string; failure_message: string; frames_url: string; imu_url: string; manifest_url: string; ready_at: string; sequence: number; status: 'recording' | 'verifying' | 'ready' | 'failed'; updated_at: string; video_url: string; }[]; capture_filename: string; captured_clip_count: number; captured_duration_seconds: number; city: string; content: string; country: string; created_at: string; deliverable_type: 'content_url' | 'media' | 'data_capture'; deliverable_urls: string[]; denial_reason: string; device: string; fov: number; operator: string; resolved_at: string; site: string; station: string; status: 'in_progress' | 'submitted' | 'approved' | 'denied'; submitted_at: string; updated_at: string; worker: { id: string; name: string; profile_picture: { url: string; }; username: string; }; }`\n\n  - `id: string`\n  - `bounty_id: string`\n  - `capture_clips: { id: string; bounty_submission_id: string; created_at: string; duration_seconds: number; failure_code: string; failure_message: string; frames_url: string; imu_url: string; manifest_url: string; ready_at: string; sequence: number; status: 'recording' | 'verifying' | 'ready' | 'failed'; updated_at: string; video_url: string; }[]`\n  - `capture_filename: string`\n  - `captured_clip_count: number`\n  - `captured_duration_seconds: number`\n  - `city: string`\n  - `content: string`\n  - `country: string`\n  - `created_at: string`\n  - `deliverable_type: 'content_url' | 'media' | 'data_capture'`\n  - `deliverable_urls: string[]`\n  - `denial_reason: string`\n  - `device: string`\n  - `fov: number`\n  - `operator: string`\n  - `resolved_at: string`\n  - `site: string`\n  - `station: string`\n  - `status: 'in_progress' | 'submitted' | 'approved' | 'denied'`\n  - `submitted_at: string`\n  - `updated_at: string`\n  - `worker: { id: string; name: string; profile_picture: { url: string; }; username: string; }`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Whop from '@whop/sdk';\n\nconst client = new Whop();\n\nconst bountySubmission = await client.bountySubmissions.create({ bounty_id: 'bounty_id' });\n\nconsole.log(bountySubmission);\n```",
