      "## estimate_reach\n\n`client.adGroups.estimateReach(platform: 'meta', account_id?: string, audiences?: { exclude?: string[]; include?: string[]; }, demographics?: { automatic?: boolean; gender?: 'all' | 'male' | 'female'; maximum_age?: number; minimum_age?: number; }, detailed_targeting?: { behaviors?: { id: string; name?: string; }[]; demographics?: { id: string; type: 'life_events' | 'industries' | 'income' | 'family_statuses'; name?: string; }[]; interests?: { id: string; name?: string; }[]; }, devices?: { operating_systems?: { os: 'ios' | 'android'; minimum_version?: string; }[]; platforms?: 'mobile' | 'desktop'[]; }, languages?: string[], regions?: { exclude?: { cities?: object[]; countries?: string[]; country_groups?: string[]; custom_locations?: object[]; regions?: string[]; zips?: string | object[]; }; include?: { cities?: object[]; countries?: string[]; country_groups?: string[]; custom_locations?: object[]; regions?: string[]; zips?: string | object[]; }; }, Idempotency-Key?: string): { users_lower_bound: number; users_upper_bound: number; }`\n\n**post** `/ad_groups/estimate_reach`\n\nEstimates how many people a draft targeting spec can reach, before an ad group is created. The body takes the same targeting fields as creating an ad group — `regions`, `demographics`, `detailed_targeting`, `audiences`, `languages`, and `devices` — and nothing is persisted.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `platform: 'meta'`\n  The ad network the estimate runs on.\n\n- `account_id?: string`\n  Account to estimate on behalf of. Defaults to the authenticated account.\n\n- `audiences?: { exclude?: string[]; include?: string[]; }`\n  Saved audiences to deliver to or exclude. Can't be combined with demographics.automatic.\n  - `exclude?: string[]`\n    IDs of saved audiences to exclude from delivery, prefixed `adaud_`.\n  - `include?: string[]`\n    IDs of saved audiences to deliver to, prefixed `adaud_`.\n\n- `demographics?: { automatic?: boolean; gender?: 'all' | 'male' | 'female'; maximum_age?: number; minimum_age?: number; }`\n  Age, gender, and automatic-audience targeting.\n  - `automatic?: boolean`\n    Turn on automatic audience targeting (Advantage+ on Meta): the platform can deliver beyond the ages, genders, and detailed targeting you set, treating them as suggestions.\n  - `gender?: 'all' | 'male' | 'female'`\n    Gender to target.\n  - `maximum_age?: number`\n    Oldest age to target.\n  - `minimum_age?: number`\n    Youngest age to target.\n\n- `detailed_targeting?: { behaviors?: { id: string; name?: string; }[]; demographics?: { id: string; type: 'life_events' | 'industries' | 'income' | 'family_statuses'; name?: string; }[]; interests?: { id: string; name?: string; }[]; }`\n  Interest, behavior, and demographic targeting, using categories from the ad platform's targeting taxonomy. At most 100 entries per section.\n  - `behaviors?: { id: string; name?: string; }[]`\n    Behavior categories to target, such as frequent travelers.\n  - `demographics?: { id: string; type: 'life_events' | 'industries' | 'income' | 'family_statuses'; name?: string; }[]`\n    Demographic categories to target, such as life events or industries.\n  - `interests?: { id: string; name?: string; }[]`\n    Interest categories to target, such as an interest in movies.\n\n- `devices?: { operating_systems?: { os: 'ios' | 'android'; minimum_version?: string; }[]; platforms?: 'mobile' | 'desktop'[]; }`\n  Device platforms and operating systems to target.\n  - `operating_systems?: { os: 'ios' | 'android'; minimum_version?: string; }[]`\n    Operating systems to target. Empty targets all operating systems.\n  - `platforms?: 'mobile' | 'desktop'[]`\n    Device types to target. Empty targets all devices.\n\n- `languages?: string[]`\n  Languages to target, as ISO 639 codes such as `en` or `es`. Empty or omitted targets all languages.\n\n- `regions?: { exclude?: { cities?: { key: string; name?: string; }[]; countries?: string[]; country_groups?: string[]; custom_locations?: { latitude: number; longitude: number; radius: number; distance_unit?: 'mile' | 'kilometer'; name?: string; }[]; regions?: string[]; zips?: string | { key: string; }[]; }; include?: { cities?: { key: string; name?: string; }[]; countries?: string[]; country_groups?: string[]; custom_locations?: { latitude: number; longitude: number; radius: number; distance_unit?: 'mile' | 'kilometer'; name?: string; }[]; regions?: string[]; zips?: string | { key: string; }[]; }; }`\n  Locations to target and exclude.\n  - `exclude?: { cities?: { key: string; name?: string; }[]; countries?: string[]; country_groups?: string[]; custom_locations?: { latitude: number; longitude: number; radius: number; distance_unit?: 'mile' | 'kilometer'; name?: string; }[]; regions?: string[]; zips?: string | { key: string; }[]; }`\n    Locations excluded from targeting. Country groups can't be excluded.\n  - `include?: { cities?: { key: string; name?: string; }[]; countries?: string[]; country_groups?: string[]; custom_locations?: { latitude: number; longitude: number; radius: number; distance_unit?: 'mile' | 'kilometer'; name?: string; }[]; regions?: string[]; zips?: string | { key: string; }[]; }`\n    Locations the ad group targets.\n\n- `Idempotency-Key?: string`\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ users_lower_bound: number; users_upper_bound: number; }`\n\n  - `users_lower_bound: number`\n  - `users_upper_bound: number`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Whop from '@whop/sdk';\n\nconst client = new Whop();\n\nconst reachEstimate = await client.adGroups.estimateReach({ platform: 'meta' });\n\nconsole.log(reachEstimate);\n```",
